New Meet on the STREET LEGAL podcast with @tryingosling complete with his graphic but accurate rendition of the @lacklusterpod backstory and my sudden realization that @headgum may be generating the space time continuum itself as Posted @withregram ‚Ä¢ @lacklusterpod from @tryingosling : A couple of years ago I was eating butternut squash soup on a patio with my brother and said ‚ÄúI‚Äôm telling you Bogus Journey is better- oh shit, I think that‚Äôs Finn Wolfhard.‚Äù I was right. Bogus Journey is better. Also it was Finn Wolfhard. I asked him if he liked Jake and Amir even though I knew the answer was yes and we talked for a few minutes about our favourite movies and comedians. Then he had to go to a record signing and I had to get back to my butternut squash soup so we parted ways. Cut to a year later. I‚Äôm eating lunch my first day on set of a movie and I don‚Äôt really know anyone yet. Finn sits down across from me and says ‚ÄúHey man, I‚Äôm Finn. Do I know you?‚Äù ‚ÄúWe actually met very briefly in Toront-‚Äú ‚ÄúOh shit, you‚Äôre the Jake and Amir kid!‚Äù We picked up our conversation where it left off and kind of never stopped talking. Another year-ish later we have a show together on Jake and Amir‚Äôs podcast network and it‚Äôs us still talking about our favourite movies and comedians. It‚Äôs a really surreal and lovely and bizarre full circle thing that I‚Äôm super grateful for. Two guys sitting at their desks are responsible for my entire sense of humour and half of my friendships. I‚Äôm really grateful for that too. ‚ÄúOh shit, you‚Äôre the Jake and Amir kid!‚Äù I was the Jake and Amir kid. And so was Finn. We both still are. Lackluster Video 02 comes out TODAY. Special Guest: Amir Valerie Blumenfeld himself. üíôüíõ

Posted @withregram ‚Ä¢ @panavisionofficial "Rules For Werewolves was shot on the Panaflex Platinum and the ultra-speedy Ultra Speeds supplied by Panavision Vancouver. I was introduced to the Ultra Speeds using them on commercials and fell in love.‚Å£
‚Å£
It was a no-brainer to employ them on this film as Jeremy and I wanted a gritty look for the world of werewolves and our small lighting budget required some quick glass. We shot everything at a T2 where the lenses perform beautifully with the perfect amount of grit, even more so when paired with 2-perf 5219."‚Å£

This doc made me really appreciate my generation.  There are good people among us. @boysstatemovie

@kodak_shootfilm ‚ÄúSome version of this team have joined up about once a year to work together for multiple years now, and there's a communal bond and artistic communication that's really strong. It's something so lovely and invigorating that I find myself trying to cook up new projects just for the opportunity¬†to be a part of it again.
‚†Ä
Cole has this great relaxed, focused presence on set while somehow bringing a spontaneous energy to what he puts onscreen. His lighting and his camera are such exciting storytellers and performers that I find myself setting the stage and then stepping back to enjoy the interplay of him navigating the scene alongside our cast. I think shooting on film gave us the most beautiful but raw way to capture those discoveries on set. Not totally sure how to put it into words but it feels like film created the least separation between the story and the audience.
‚†Ä
There's a timeless feeling in the emulsion as well as an on-set vitality that shooting on film creates, both of which really worked well with our teen werewolves!‚Äù
‚†Ä
